      "body": "# feat(scenarios): Implement conditional mocking and complex response structures

## Description

This ticket enhances the mocking system to support conditional responses based on input parameters and complex response structures with metadata. This enables realistic testing of service interactions like GitHub API calls or EVM transactions with proper request/response matching.

## Acceptance Criteria

1. Mock definitions support `when` clauses for conditional responses
2. `when` clauses can match on method arguments, input parameters, or request context
3. Mock responses support complex nested structures with metadata (timestamps, IDs, etc.)
4. Multiple mock responses can be defined for the same service/method with different conditions
5. Mock system provides clear logging of which mock was triggered and why
6. Mock responses can include realistic error conditions and edge cases
7. Support for dynamic response generation based on input parameters
8. Mock validation ensures `when` clauses are syntactically correct

## Technical Approach

### 1. Enhanced Mock Schema
```typescript
// packages/cli/src/scenarios/schema.ts
const MockSchema = z.object({
  service: z.string(),
  method: z.string(),
  when: z.object({
    // Match on method arguments
    args: z.array(z.any()).optional(),
    // Match on specific argument values
    input: z.record(z.any()).optional(),
    // Match on request context
    context: z.record(z.any()).optional(),
    // Custom matching function
    matcher: z.string().optional(), // JavaScript expression
  }).optional(),
  response: z.any(), // Can be function or static value
  // For dynamic responses
  responseFn: z.string().optional(), // JavaScript function
  // Error simulation
  error: z.object({
    code: z.string(),
    message: z.string(),
  }).optional(),
});
```

### 2. Mock Engine Implementation
```typescript
// packages/cli/src/scenarios/mock-engine.ts
export class MockEngine {
  private mocks: MockDefinition[] = [];

  addMock(mock: MockDefinition) {
    this.mocks.push(mock);
  }

  async findMock(service: string, method: string, args: any[]): Promise<any> {
    const candidates = this.mocks.filter(m => 
      m.service === service && m.method === method
    );

    for (const mock of candidates) {
      if (await this.matchesCondition(mock, args)) {
        this.logger.info(`Mock triggered: ${service}.${method} with condition: ${JSON.stringify(mock.when)}`);
        return this.generateResponse(mock, args);
      }
    }

    return null; // No mock found
  }

  private async matchesCondition(mock: MockDefinition, args: any[]): Promise<boolean> {
    if (!mock.when) return true; // Default mock

    // Match on arguments
    if (mock.when.args) {
      if (!this.deepEqual(args, mock.when.args)) return false;
    }

    // Match on input parameters
    if (mock.when.input) {
      const input = this.extractInputFromArgs(args);
      if (!this.deepEqual(input, mock.when.input)) return false;
    }

    // Custom matcher function
    if (mock.when.matcher) {
      const matcherFn = new Function('args', 'input', mock.when.matcher);
      return matcherFn(args, this.extractInputFromArgs(args));
    }

    return true;
  }

  private generateResponse(mock: MockDefinition, args: any[]): any {
    if (mock.error) {
      throw new Error(`${mock.error.code}: ${mock.error.message}`);
    }

    if (mock.responseFn) {
      const responseFn = new Function('args', 'input', mock.responseFn);
      return responseFn(args, this.extractInputFromArgs(args));
    }

    return mock.response;
  }
}
```

